article_title: Benefits for American Indians available in the health care marketplace

og.description: Deep in our nation’s history, federal leaders created legal agreements with the American Indian people regarding health care for members of various tribes. Treaties, laws, Supreme Court cases, executive orders and the constitution all outline the government-to-government relationship between the United States and the federally recognized tribes. But tribal health care insurance program providers say the more modern Affordable Care Act strengthens those promises and provides expanded opportunities not only for individual American Indians, but also for the Indian Health Services many natives rely on for primary health care provisions.
